Commonly encountered adrenal pseudotumours on CT. There are a variety of causes of adrenal pseudotumours on CT, including gastric diverticulum, prominent splenic lobulation, upper-pole renal mass, pancreatic mass, hepatic mass and periadrenal varices. These adrenal pseudotumours can be elucidated by multiplanar reconstruction using CT and MRI as well as from the axial images.